# Family Hub — environment template
#
# Copy to .env.local and fill in. .env.local is gitignored.
# Place at the REPO ROOT (not apps/api/). The api dev script loads it via
# --env-file=../../.env.local. In production (Railway) envs are injected
# by the platform — this file is for local dev + as a contract of what
# every service needs.
#
# This file MUST NEVER contain real secret values. Real values live in:
#   - Railway dashboard → Service → Variables (production + staging)
#   - Stripe / Supabase / Sentry dashboards (source of truth for API keys)
#   - your local .env.local (gitignored) for dev
# A shared password vault is a future follow-up — not yet ticketed; not
# needed while the project is solo.

# ─── Runtime ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
NODE_ENV=development                    # development | staging | production
PORT=3001                               # api listens on this port locally
LOG_LEVEL=info                          # debug | info | warn | error (pino)

# ─── Domain + security middleware (FHS-170) ───────────────────────────────
# Used by api for cookie domain, CORS allowlist, and tenant-slug subdomain
# resolution (ADR 0002). Locally: localhost. Staging: staging.familyhub.app.
# Production: familyhub.app.
BASE_DOMAIN=localhost
VITE_API_URL=http://localhost:3001      # frontend reads this at build time
# Comma-separated explicit override for CORS. Empty = derive from BASE_DOMAIN
# (apex + *.subdomains, http + https). Set when you need to allow a third
# party (e.g. Storybook on a separate host).
# CORS_ALLOWED_ORIGINS=
# Token-bucket rate limit per IP per minute. 0 disables (test runs).
# RATE_LIMIT_PER_MINUTE=100

# ─── Postgres ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Local dev: docker-compose Postgres (./scripts/dev or `pnpm dev:up`) on
# :5432 with familyhub/familyhub credentials. Railway-hosted Postgres
# injects DATABASE_URL automatically — do not paste real values here.
# Test DB runs on :5433 with fh_test/fh_test — see tests/integration/support/db.ts.
DATABASE_URL=postgres://familyhub:familyhub@localhost:5432/familyhub_dev
# DATABASE_URL_TEST=postgres://fh_test:fh_test@localhost:5433/familyhub_test

# ─── Auth (FHS-178 epic — Supabase) ────────────────────────────────────────
# Two projects, one per Railway env (see docs/decisions/0008-supabase-environments.md).
# Migrate to a single project + 'staging' branch when the org upgrades to Pro.
# Obtain values from Supabase dashboard → Project Settings → API.
#
# Personal Access Token for the Supabase management API (api.supabase.com):
# https://supabase.com/dashboard/account/tokens
# SUPABASE_ACCESS_TOKEN=
#
# Per-environment project credentials.
# Staging project: maolytpqazmykjzdybtj  (Family Hub Staging)
# SUPABASE_URL_STAGING=https://maolytpqazmykjzdybtj.supabase.co
# SUPABASE_ANON_KEY_STAGING=
# SUPABASE_SERVICE_ROLE_KEY_STAGING=     # server-side only, never expose to web
# SUPABASE_PUBLISHABLE_KEY_STAGING=      # new asymmetric (sb_publishable_...) — optional
# SUPABASE_SECRET_KEY_STAGING=           # new asymmetric (sb_secret_...) — optional, server-side
# SUPABASE_DB_PASSWORD_STAGING=          # Postgres superuser password (rotate via dashboard)
#
# Production project: bqghmbkoxjompuxixexn  (Family Hub Production)
# SUPABASE_URL_PRODUCTION=https://bqghmbkoxjompuxixexn.supabase.co
# SUPABASE_ANON_KEY_PRODUCTION=
# SUPABASE_SERVICE_ROLE_KEY_PRODUCTION=
# SUPABASE_PUBLISHABLE_KEY_PRODUCTION=
# SUPABASE_SECRET_KEY_PRODUCTION=
#
# Local dev defaults — point these at staging unless you specifically need prod.
# Most dotenv loaders (Vite, Node `--env-file`) do NOT expand `$VAR` references —
# paste the resolved value here, not `$SUPABASE_URL_STAGING`.
#
# On Railway each environment is bound to exactly one Supabase project
# (staging Railway env ↔ staging Supabase, prod Railway env ↔ prod Supabase),
# so the api/web only ever read the unsuffixed `SUPABASE_*` / `VITE_SUPABASE_*`
# names below. The `_STAGING`/`_PRODUCTION` pairs above are local-dev-only.
# Real Railway values are managed per env via the Railway dashboard / MCP —
# see FHS-189 and docs/technical/deployment.md.
# SUPABASE_URL=https://maolytpqazmykjzdybtj.supabase.co
# SUPABASE_ANON_KEY=
# SUPABASE_SERVICE_ROLE_KEY=
#
# Web bundle (apps/web) — only client-safe values. NEVER paste service_role
# or secret keys behind a `VITE_` prefix; those leak into the browser bundle.
# VITE_SUPABASE_URL=https://maolytpqazmykjzdybtj.supabase.co
# VITE_SUPABASE_ANON_KEY=
# VITE_SUPABASE_PUBLISHABLE_KEY=         # optional; modern asymmetric (sb_publishable_...)
#
# AUTH_SECRET is the JWT signing secret used by the api to verify tokens
# minted by Supabase. Modern Supabase uses ES256 (asymmetric) — verify via
# the JWKS endpoint at $SUPABASE_URL/auth/v1/.well-known/jwks.json instead
# of a shared secret. Set AUTH_SECRET only if running auth locally without
# Supabase (e.g., legacy HS256 path). Generate with `openssl rand -base64 48`.
# AUTH_SECRET=

# ─── Stripe (FHS-68 epic — billing, Sprint 4) ──────────────────────────────
# Obtain from Stripe dashboard → Developers → API keys (test mode for dev).
# STRIPE_SECRET_KEY=                     # sk_test_… (dev) / sk_live_… (prod)
# STRIPE_WEBHOOK_SECRET=                 # whsec_… from Stripe CLI or dashboard
# STRIPE_PUBLISHABLE_KEY=                # pk_test_… exposed to web

# ─── Sentry (FHS-166 — observability) ──────────────────────────────────────
# Obtain from Sentry dashboard → Project Settings → Client Keys (DSN).
# Two projects: api (Node runtime) + web (browser). Either var alone
# satisfies the "Sentry DSN" contract for its surface; both empty =
# silent no-op (SDK loaded, no events sent).
# SENTRY_DSN_API=
# VITE_SENTRY_DSN_WEB=                  # build-time-baked into apps/web bundle
# SENTRY_RELEASE=                       # git SHA — set by CI/Railway, not locally
# VITE_SENTRY_RELEASE=                  # mirror SENTRY_RELEASE on the web build
# SENTRY_TRACES_SAMPLE_RATE=0.1         # api perf sample rate; 0..1
# VITE_SENTRY_TRACES_SAMPLE_RATE=0.1    # web perf sample rate
#
# Source map upload (CI only — never set these locally):
# SENTRY_AUTH_TOKEN=                    # https://<sentry>/settings/account/api/auth-tokens
# SENTRY_ORG=                           # Sentry org slug
# SENTRY_PROJECT_WEB=                   # web project slug

# ─── Jira ↔ GitHub automation (used by /tmp/*.py scripts, not the api) ─────
# Obtain Jira API token from https://id.atlassian.com/manage-profile/security/api-tokens.
# EMAIL=you@example.com
# JIRA_API_TOKEN=
# URL=https://qualicion2.atlassian.net/

# ─── E2E test user (FHS-196 — Playwright login flow) ───────────────────────
# Synthetic Supabase user dedicated to e2e tests; never log in as this in
# the dashboard for real work. Provisioned out-of-band against the staging
# Supabase project — see infra/supabase/README.md for the create/rotate
# script. Locally: keep in .env.local. CI: set as repo secrets
# (E2E_USER_EMAIL, E2E_USER_PASSWORD); the e2e workflow exports them into
# the runner env before invoking Playwright.
# E2E_USER_EMAIL=e2e@familyhub.test
# E2E_USER_PASSWORD=

# ─── Railway (FHS-156 — Railway MCP server in .mcp.json) ───────────────────
# Mint at https://railway.com/account/tokens (Account Tokens, not Project).
# .mcp.json is gitignored; each contributor adds their own MCP via:
#   claude mcp add railway --scope local --env RAILWAY_API_TOKEN=$RAILWAY_API_TOKEN \
#       -- npx -y @jasontanswe/railway-mcp
# RAILWAY_API_TOKEN=
